		<div id="welcome">

			<h4>*STAGE 1: CATEGORIES, TERMS, CONCEPTS AND SPECIFIC OBJECTS*</h4>
		 	<br />

			Each or any of the <i>terms, concept or specific objects</i> may invoke personal feelings, spark a particular philosophical interest, connect with you on spiritual level, all three or none at all. Based on your understanding of the term [word] chosen, it’s up to you to reflect on your life’s experience and select the category, or categories, you feel best fit it.
			<br /><br />
			<ul class="about">
				<li>Dragging the mouse towards the dark corner suggests a higher degree of spirituality (has substance but is not relatable or not understandable)</li>
				<li>Dragging the mouse towards the base color suggests something more material (concrete, relatable or understandable)</li>
				<li>Dragging the mouse towards white and the spiritual & material begin to converge, attaining parity at the vertex.</li>
			</ul>
			<br />
			<img src="img/s1Img.jpg" style="float:left; margin:0 20px 15px 0;"/>
			<div>
				<strong><a href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#reminder">Select up to 4 categories</a> for any given <i>term, concept or specific object</i>:</strong><br /><br />
				<ul class="about">
					<li>Man's View of Himself/Herself (abbreviated to 'Himself')</li>
					<li>Man's Connections with Other than Himself</li>
					<li>Man's View of the World</li>
					<li>Man's Physical Activities</li>
				</ul>
				<strong>The word "Man" simply means the <i>universal man</i> of which you are an example. As such, you may:</strong><br /><br />
            	<ul class="about">
					<li>Personalize any or all <i>terms, concepts or specific objects</i> to yourself</li>
					<li>Think of others exclusively</li>
					<li>Think of yourself and others together</li>
            	</ul>
			</div>
			There are no right or wrong answers here since the goal of Ybigh is to map your individual personality. Yes, to project your mind into the machine.
		</div>
